N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 4103.8 - Charts

State Regulations

Each program shall print an official chart of the latest
preceding night's results available. Such chart shall indicate any horses
scratched and the reason therefor, broken equipment of a horse not causing a
break, that a horse's performance has been materially affected because it
choked down, the average weather temperature for the program, and other factual
information that may be deemed necessary by the commission from time to
time. Notes
